### Step 1: Install the Kernel Module
Make sure you have compiled and installed your Linux kernel module correctly. You can do this by following these commands in a terminal:

```bash
# Navigate to the directory containing your kernel module source code
cd /path/to/your/module

# Compile the module (make sure you have necessary build tools)
make

# Install the module
sudo make install

# Load the module into memory
sudo modprobe <module_name>
```

### Step 2: Verify Module Installation 
You can check if your driver is loaded using:

```bash
lsmod | grep <module_name>
```

